<a NAME="Overview"></a><font face="Arial, Helvetica">Summary/Overview</font></h3>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica">The bookmarks and history UI will enable
the user to use, browse and organize hierarchical lists of their data.
Initially the UI described here will be deployed for bookmarks and historyonly.
The general UI framwork will be consistent with managing and viewing data
throughout Communicator (such as mail and project folders). This capability
was formerly dubbed Aurora and is based on rdf technology. Initially this
will be used for data like bookmarks, site maps or email items, but can
eventually be extended to other future items as well (such as native files,
people etc)</font>
<h3> <font face="Arial, Helvetica">Goals</font></h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Provide simple integration of History and Bookmarks<br>
    Provide streamlined approach to Navigation, grouping related elements close 
    to each other<br>
    Allow simple management of bookmarks inline</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica">Target Audience</font></h3>

<blockquote><font face="Arial, Helvetica">The target user for this feature
are Communicator Seamonkey users as described in the Seamonkey PRD, but specifically
no-fuss end-users that are trying to access and organze information quickly.</font>
<h3>
</h3>
</blockquote>

